- "Points percentage" is calculated as the ratio of points earned to the total possible points in a season;
- "Defense players" are typically not known for scoring many goals, so a defense player scoring more than 15 goals is notable.

- "Performance change" in this context refers to the comparison of a team's points to the points of the team ranked just above them in the same league and season;
- "Stable" means the team has the same points as the team ranked just above them;
- "Improved" means the team has more points than the team ranked just above them;
- "Declined" means the team has fewer points than the team ranked just above them.

sql:
SELECT season_id, AVG(power_play_goals) AS average_power_play_goals
FROM team_metrics
GROUP BY season_id;

